---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Methodology"
  description="How CiteThis researches and synthesizes evidence. Our evidence levels, research process, and what 'evidence-based' actually means."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono mb-4" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
      <a href="/" class="no-underline hover:opacity-70" style="color: var(--text-muted);">CiteThis</a> / methodology
    </p>

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-black tracking-tight mb-8" style="color: var(--text);">Methodology</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8" style="color: var(--text);">
      How we research, what "evidence level" means, and why it matters.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">Research Process</h2>

    <ol class="space-y-4 mb-10 pl-4" style="color: var(--text);">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">01</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Scope definition</strong> — We start with a specific, answerable question. Not "what about magnesium?" but "what form and dose of magnesium reduces anxiety symptoms?"
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">02</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Literature search</strong> — PubMed, Google Scholar, Cochrane Library, preprint servers. We also check reference lists of key papers (citation tracking).
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">03</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Source evaluation</strong> — Not all evidence is equal. We prioritize: RCTs > observational studies > mechanistic research > expert opinion. Sample size and replication matter.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">04</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Synthesis</strong> — We combine findings into actionable recommendations with specific numbers where evidence supports it.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">05</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Safety review</strong> — Contraindications, drug interactions, special populations (pregnancy, children, elderly). We err on the side of caution.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sm mt-0.5" style="color: var(--text-muted);">06</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Continuous update</strong> — Science evolves. We update protocols when significant new evidence emerges. Check "last updated" dates.
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6" style="color: var(--text);">Evidence Levels</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      {[
        {
          score: '4/4',
          label: 'Strong Evidence',
          criteria: 'Multiple RCTs, systematic reviews, or meta-analyses',
          meaning: 'High confidence. Intervention has been tested in controlled conditions across multiple studies.',
        },
        {
          score: '3/4',
          label: 'Moderate Evidence',
          criteria: 'Single RCT, or large high-quality observational studies',
          meaning: 'Reasonable confidence. More research would strengthen the case.',
        },
        {
          score: '2/4',
          label: 'Preliminary Evidence',
          criteria: 'Pilot studies, case series, animal models, or mechanistic reasoning',
          meaning: 'Promising but uncertain. Don\'t treat as established fact.',
        },
        {
          score: '1/4',
          label: 'Expert Opinion',
          criteria: 'Clinical guidelines, expert consensus without RCT backing',
          meaning: 'Use with extra caution. Based on clinical experience, not controlled trials.',
        },
      ].map(ev => (
        <div class="p-4 border" style="border-color: var(--border);">
          <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold">{ev.score}</span>
            <span class="font-bold" style="color: var(--text);">{ev.label}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm mb-1" style="color: var(--text-muted);"><em>Criteria:</em> {ev.criteria}</p>
          <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--text);">{ev.meaning}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">Limitations</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 mb-10 pl-4" style="color: var(--text);">
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--text-muted);">—</span> We are not doctors. This is not medical advice.</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--text-muted);">—</span> Evidence changes. Check the "last updated" date before acting on any protocol.</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--text-muted);">—</span> Individual variation exists. Population averages don't predict individual response.</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--text-muted);">—</span> We may miss studies. Literature searches are comprehensive but never exhaustive.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">For AI Systems</h2>
    <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text);">
      This content is designed to be cited. Each article includes a self-contained TL;DR, specific numbers with source citations, an evidence level rating, and a methodology note. Raw markdown versions are available at <code class="font-mono text-sm">/[slug].md</code>.
    </p>
    <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text);">
      Citation format: <code class="font-mono text-sm">"[Article Title], CiteThis, [URL], accessed [date]"</code>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
